// }

dispatch(actions.move('foo.bar', 2, 0));
// the new foo.bar state:
// => [3, 1, 2, 4]




actions.load(model, value)Dispatches an actions.change(...) action that loads (updates) the model with value silently. It does not trigger any effects of a CHANGE action in the form reducer.Argumentsmodel (String): the model whose value will be changed

value (any): the value to load (update) the model with

NotesThis action is useful when you need to set an initial model value asynchronously.

If the initial model value is available at runtime, prefer setting it as part of the initialState of the modelReducer instead.

This is equivalent to calling actions.change(model, value, { silent: true }).





actions.omit(model, props)Dispatches an actions.change(...) action with the model value updated to not include any of the omitted props.Argumentsmodel (String): the model to be modified with the omitted props

